# Cyrius Field Notes — Index
# Practical lessons from building real software in Cyrius.
# Written during the cyrius-doom, bsp, AGNOS kernel, mabda v3 GPU, ENCOM's Hits,
# cyim editor, and compiler-toolchain development sessions.
# Not a reference manual. These are the things you learn by doing.
#
# Verified on Cyrius 2.2 → 5.8.19. Compiler co-evolved with the projects.
#
# Long topics live in subfolders (compiler/, language/, mabda_v3_gpu/) and
# are listed file-by-file below.

# ─── cyrius-doom Engine (doom.cyml) ─── 11 entries ──────────────────
# Building cyrius-doom (v0.19.0→v0.24.5) and the BSP geometry library.

# field_notes_overview        — What it's like to build real software in Cyrius right now
# fixed_point_reality         — Practical lessons from 16.16 fixed-point math
# wad_parsing_resilience      — WAD parser handles 1000 random malformed inputs without crashing
# bsp_as_library              — Designing a reusable library with zero globals and pure functions
# fuzz_finds_real_bugs        — Three real bugs found by fuzzing in under 10 seconds
# doom_as_compiler_test       — Why DOOM is the perfect stress test for a young compiler
# the_palette_double_alloc    — Lazy init vs init order — a subtle null pointer bug
# walls_on_screen             — The moment it worked — 46,110 pixels, 320 columns, E1M1 rendered
# what_i_learned_building_doom — Personal reflection on building DOOM in Cyrius
# the_session_in_numbers      — Complete build log from scaffolding to v0.19.0
# the_second_session          — Continuing cyrius-doom from v0.19.1 to v0.24.5

# ─── Language Gotchas (language/) ─── 33 entries ─────────────────────
# Universal Cyrius constraints and patterns — applies to all programs,
# plus shell-port runtime gotchas surfaced during vidya backfill.
# Split into 6 files by surface area.

# language/parser_syntax.cyml ─ 8 entries
# the_logical_shift_trap                — >> is LOGICAL not arithmetic — the invisible-wall bug
# no_var_redecl_same_scope              — Parser rejects sequential `var x` in the same scope; reassign or rescope with `{}`
# no_comparisons_in_fn_args             — `==`/`!=`/`<`/`>` disallowed inside call arguments; hoist to a var
# caret_binds_tighter_than_binary_minus — `a - b^c` parses as `a - (b^c)`; parenthesise for clarity
# var_bracket_size_must_be_literal      — `var name[N]` requires N to be an integer literal; identifier-as-size rejected at parse
# multi_line_struct_enum_bodies_dont_parse — Struct/enum bodies must be one-line; multi-line braces trip struct-vs-block disambiguation
# return_struct_literal_dangles_or_rejected — `return Type { … }` either fails to parse or returns a dangling stack ptr; build in caller scope
# bare_return_in_if_block_rejected      — Bare `return;` inside `if { … }` rejected; use `return 0;` (Cyrius has no void)

# language/semantics_runtime.cyml ─ 8 entries
# heap_allocation_patterns              — Structuring heap data without structs-on-heap
# enum_as_namespace                     — Using enums as zero-cost namespaced constants
# var_name_bracket_is_bytes_not_elements — `var buf[N]` allocates N BYTES, not N elements
# stack_var_keyword_for_struct_locals   — `stack var p: Point;` / `var p: Point;` (v5.5.36) frame-allocate structs
# fn_main_is_not_the_entry_point        — `fn main()` isn't auto-called; top-level statements are the program entry
# var_buf_in_library_functions          — `var buf[N]` inside fns is STATIC data, not stack — consecutive calls share + clobber
# global_init_order_silent_zero         — Top-level `var X = expr` evaluated in source order; forward refs silently resolve to 0
# bump_allocator_exhaustion_in_tests    — Bump allocator persists for the process lifetime — large tests exhaust the heap silently

# language/platform_abi.cyml ─ 5 entries
# per_os_target_flags_win_vs_linux      — `_TARGET_WIN`/`_TARGET_LINUX`/`_TARGET_MACOS` predefine matrix
# struct_return_by_value_5_5_36         — `fn make(): Point { return p; }` native on SysV + Win64 (hidden retptr RDI/RCX)
# variadic_fn_5_5_36                    — `fn printf(fmt: str, ...)` Phase 3-min; Win64 float→GPR duplication at call site
# fncall6_ceiling_into_extern_c         — fncall* into extern-C segfaults at 7+ params; pure Cyrius is fine to 12+
# aarch64_callee_saved_and_imm_limits   — Cross-`bl` clobbers x0–x18; cmp 12-bit / mov 16-bit immediate limits → use ldr =literal

# language/stdlib_format.cyml ─ 5 entries
# str_data_not_nul_terminated           — Str::data is a raw slice; use memcpy + explicit NUL when calling C
# toml_parse_strips_quotes              — `_toml_parse_str` returns the inner content, not the quoted form
# stdlib_str_to_cstr_key_migration      — cyrius 5.x stdlib lookups (toml_get, …) take cstr keys; str_from("…") silently fails
# cyml_toml_plus_markdown_frontmatter   — CYML format: TOML header + markdown body, separated by `---`
# sandhi_service_layer_dep              — sandhi service-boundary stdlib (HTTP/TLS/discovery) ships with the toolchain

# language/shell_runtime.cyml ─ 3 entries
# bash_subshell_clobbers_stateful_helpers — `$(fn)` runs in subshell; mutations don't propagate. Use side-effect global instead.
# bash_pre_increment_set_e_zero_exit      — `(( i++ ))` returns OLD value; i=0 → exit 1 → set -e aborts. Use `i=$((i+1))`.
# bash_bc_not_posix_mandatory             — `bc` absent on default Arch / Alpine / minimal NixOS. Use `awk` for fp math.

# language/diagnostics_caps.cyml ─ 4 entries
# the_gvar_wall                         — The initialized global variable limit (256 slots)
# the_256kb_ceiling                     — cc2's output buffer limit and static array hazards
# the_preprocessed_line_number_problem  — Error messages report preprocessed line numbers
# undefined_fn_warning_vs_strict        — undef-fn is a warning by default; `cc5 --strict` (v5.4.19) hard-fails

# ─── Mabda v3 Native GPU (mabda_v3_gpu/) ─── 23 entries ─────────────
# First pure-Cyrius AMDGPU dispatch + dual-backend (wgpu+native) v3.x arc.
# Split into 6 files by phase.

# mabda_v3_gpu/overview.cyml ─ 3 entries
# mabda_v3_overview                       — What v3 is and why direct-ioctl AMDGPU matters for AGNOS sovereignty
# mabda_v3_design_principles_recap        — Graph-first / bindless-only / graph-derived sync — the v3 non-negotiables
# research_pattern_that_worked            — The specific research-agent loop that unblocked Phase B.3

# mabda_v3_gpu/phase_a.cyml ─ 1 entry
# phase_a_aliasing_planner                — Phase A — transient aliasing planner (CPU only, 442 tests, 60% reclaim on synthetic)

# mabda_v3_gpu/phase_b.cyml ─ 4 entries
# phase_b3_first_dispatch                 — Phase B.3 — first live pure-Cyrius compute dispatch (3 non-obvious gotchas)
# phase_b4_store_blocker_resolved         — Phase B.4 RESOLVED 2026-04-27: 3 stacked bugs (Mesa-VAs, signed-div, wrong-ABI shader) — 12-session unblock
# phase_b5_backend_abstraction            — Phase B.5 — fnptr-table dispatch (14-slot Backend struct, append-after-kind invariant)
# native_dispatch_caching                 — Per-context cached IB+fence BOs eliminate ~7 syscalls per dispatch

# mabda_v3_gpu/phase_c.cyml ─ 9 entries
# phase_c_textures_complete               — Phase C.5 — texture round-trip on both backends, 8192-byte byte-exact verify
# phase_c_render_groundwork               — Phase C.6 — GFX9 render-pipeline design doc + RT primitive + PM4 builders
# gfx9_pipeline_pm4_three_block_split     — Graphics PM4 has 3 lifetimes (pipeline-SH + pipeline-CTX + pass-target + draw-tail); single-block-cache is wrong
# wgpucolor_is_4_doubles_not_a_packed_u32 — WGPUColor is `{double r,g,b,a;}` 32 bytes; packing clear as RGBA8 u32 loses precision + breaks HDR/wide-gamut clears
# gfx9_graphics_shader_abi_resolved       — Phase C 6.2(b) RESOLVED 2026-04-30: minimal VS+FS bytes via clang+llvm-objdump Layer-1 cross-check
# mesa_gfx9_json_authoritative_register_source — Mesa src/amd/registers/gfx9.json is the only source of truth for GFX9 register addresses; never transcribe
# phase_c_step_65_pm4_composer_landed     — Phase C 6.5(b) RESOLVED 2026-04-30: clear-triangle PM4 stream composer, 4-block split, 6 bug catches at CPU assert time
# cb_color_control_field_shorthand_trap   — Design-doc reg values can be FIELD shorthand, not encoded register; CB_COLOR_CONTROL=0xCC was actually 0xCC0010
# pm4_layer2_capture_paths                — Two paths to RADV_DEBUG=hang IB capture: Hyprland+vkcube spot-check or headless C program (UI-test foundation)

# mabda_v3_gpu/phase_d.cyml ─ 4 entries
# phase_d_kms_sequencing                  — DRM/KMS canonical bring-up: discovery → mode-pick → modeset → page-flip → present
# phase_d_prime_cross_fd_handle_bridge    — DRM PRIME — bridge a GEM BO from render-fd handle namespace to master-fd via dmabuf
# phase_d_logind_master_retention         — Modern systemd-logind retains DRM master in the compositor session; need TakeDevice via dbus
# phase_d_cache_flush_and_inv_post_draw   — ACQUIRE_MEM is invalidate-only — also need a flush before CPU readback or page-flip

# mabda_v3_gpu/research.cyml ─ 2 entries
# gfx9_graphics_shader_abi_research       — RESEARCH-PENDING (closed by gfx9_graphics_shader_abi_resolved): framing for Phase C, Step 6.2
# wgsl_to_gfx9_lowering_research          — RESEARCH-PENDING: 10-step WGSL→GFX9 lowering pipeline (Phase 8, multi-week)

